  "texts": [
    "The design phase constitutes the second stage in the architectural design process.",
    "It involves the development of conceptual plans for the building layout, form, and function.",
    "During the design phase, expectations encompass creating design alternatives, evaluating precedents, and existing designs, refining the design, and generating a foundational set of architectural drawings.",
    "The information extracted from the preceding stages serves as inputs for this phase.",
    "In this stage, the design concept is refined, and detailed design drawings are prepared to illustrate both 2D and 3D design solutions."
